.TH ABRAFLEXI-MCP-START 1 "February 2026" "1.0.1" "AbraFlexi MCP Server Manual"
.SH NAME
abraflexi-mcp-start \- validate environment and start the AbraFlexi MCP server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B abraflexi-mcp-start
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B abraflexi-mcp-start
is a startup wrapper for the AbraFlexi MCP server.
It validates that all required environment variables are set, prints the
current configuration summary, and then launches the MCP server.
.PP
The script checks for the following before starting the server:
.IP \(bu 2
Required variables \fBABRAFLEXI_URL\fR and \fBABRAFLEXI_COMPANY\fR.
.IP \(bu 2
Authentication configuration (session ID or username/password).
.IP \(bu 2
Transport mode validity (\fBstdio\fR or \fBstreamable-http\fR).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_URL
URL of the AbraFlexi server (required).
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_COMPANY
Company identifier in AbraFlexi (required).
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_LOGIN
Username for authentication.
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_PASSWORD
Password for authentication.
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_AUTHSESSID
Session ID for authentication (alternative to login/password).
.TP
.B ABRAFLEXI_MCP_TRANSPORT
Transport mode: \fBstdio\fR (default) or \fBstreamable-http\fR.
.TP
.B READ_ONLY
Enable read-only mode (default: true).
.TP
.B DEBUG
Enable debug logging.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/abraflexi-mcp-server/.env.example
Example environment variable configuration file.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Server stopped normally.
.TP
.B 1
Environment validation failed or startup error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR abraflexi-mcp (1),
.BR abraflexi-mcp-test (1)
